ormalfont \selectfont} \DeclareTextFontCommand{	extcyr}{\cyr} \pagestyle{empty} \DeclareMathSizes{10}{9}{7}{6}  egin{document} \landscape $\overline{\varepsilon }=0$ \end{document} , and this in turn implies that \documentclass{aastex} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{bm} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{pifont} \usepackage{stmaryrd} \usepackage{textcomp} \usepackage{portland,xspace} \usepackage{amsmath,amsxtra} \usepackage[OT2,OT1]{fontenc} 
