               , andR
               2is high, namely, that shifting from the homogeneous case to the heterogeneous case does not change the aggregate demand for theith risky asset. If Lintner’s argument, asserting that prices will adjust until market clearance with no short positions is obtained, is correct, the homogeneous expectations model will be consistent with the CAPM, and the heterogeneous model pricing will also converge to the same CAPM equilibrium.

